From: Rollio build <build@rollio.local>
Subject: [PATCH] external_json: honor NLOHMANN_JSON_INCLUDE_DIR

librealsense's `external_json.cmake` unconditionally clones nlohmann/json
during CMake configure. Rollio's coracam build already ships compatible
headers via the Cora SDK and points `NLOHMANN_JSON_INCLUDE_DIR` at them
in `cameras/CMakeLists.txt`. When that variable is set to a directory
that has `nlohmann/json.hpp`, skip the clone and synthesize an INTERFACE
`nlohmann_json` target wrapping those headers so the downstream
`target_link_libraries(... nlohmann_json)` calls keep working.

Idempotency marker for `make apply-librealsense-local-nlohmann-json-patch`:
the string `NLOHMANN_JSON_INCLUDE_DIR` appearing in the patched file.

---
 CMake/external_json.cmake | 21 +++++++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 21 insertions(+)

diff --git a/CMake/external_json.cmake b/CMake/external_json.cmake
--- a/CMake/external_json.cmake
+++ b/CMake/external_json.cmake
@@ -6,6 +6,27 @@ include(ExternalProject)
 # We use a function to enforce a scoped variables creation only for the build
 # (i.e turn off BUILD_SHARED_LIBS which is used on LRS build as well)
 function(get_nlohmann_json)
+
+    # Rollio patch: if NLOHMANN_JSON_INCLUDE_DIR is set and contains
+    # nlohmann/json.hpp, skip the network fetch and expose an INTERFACE
+    # target named `nlohmann_json` that wraps those headers. The Cora SDK
+    # ships compatible nlohmann/json headers; cameras/CMakeLists.txt
+    # points NLOHMANN_JSON_INCLUDE_DIR at them before adding librealsense
+    # as a subproject, so configure stays fully offline.
+    if( NLOHMANN_JSON_INCLUDE_DIR AND
+        EXISTS "${NLOHMANN_JSON_INCLUDE_DIR}/nlohmann/json.hpp" )
+        if( NOT TARGET nlohmann_json )
+            add_library( nlohmann_json INTERFACE )
+            target_include_directories( nlohmann_json
+                INTERFACE "${NLOHMANN_JSON_INCLUDE_DIR}" )
+            add_library( nlohmann_json::nlohmann_json ALIAS nlohmann_json )
+        endif()
+        message( STATUS
+            "Using local nlohmann/json from NLOHMANN_JSON_INCLUDE_DIR="
+            "${NLOHMANN_JSON_INCLUDE_DIR}" )
+        return()
+    endif()
+

     message( STATUS #CHECK_START
         "Fetching nlohmann/json..." )
